BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Speaker Series,Jewish Studies Speaker Series
DESCRIPTION:Lucy Dixon\, University of Winchester in London\, will speak on
  her research\, “Reproducing Nazism”\, which is a feminist ethical critique
  of women’s complicity in National Socialism at the intersection of materni
 ty\, care and thinking. Her work is situated within the field of Philosophy
  of Education\, as well as Holocaust education/studies and is interdiscipli
 nary by nature.\n\n \n\nJewish Studies sponsors this event.\n\n \n\nPlease 
 register to attend this virtual event.
DTEND:20260219T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T170247Z
DTSTART:20260219T170000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY: Reproducing Nazism
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50347844569651
URL:https://events.oakton.edu/event/reproducing-nazism
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Author Talks and Book Discussions
DESCRIPTION:The Oakton Library and the B.L.A.C.K. Student Success Program i
 nvite you to a compelling book discussion series featuring Black Birds in t
 he Sky: The Story and Legacy of the 1921 Tulsa Race Massacre by award-winni
 ng author Brandy Colbert. Together\, we’ll explore history\, memory\, and t
 he lasting impact of this pivotal moment in American history. The book disc
 ussion series takes place on Thursday\, January 29\, February 5\, 12\, and 
 19 at the DP Learning Commons\, Room 2425\, from 12 - 2:00 p.m. \n\n \n\nA 
 special author visit takes place on February 26 from 12:30 - 2:00 p.m. in t
 he Student Center\, Room 1530\, and via Zoom. Please register.\n\n \n\nBrin
 g your lunch\, your questions\, and join us for a meaningful conversation a
 nd learning. All are welcome!
DTEND:20260219T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T170247Z
DTSTART:20260219T180000Z
GEO:42.054993;-87.886683
LOCATION:Des Plaines Campus\, 2425
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:All Campus Book Read: Black Birds in the Sky
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51887595800454
URL:https://events.oakton.edu/event/all-campus-book-read-black-birds-in-the
 -sky
END:VEVENT
