BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Author Talks and Book Discussions
DESCRIPTION:The Oakton Library and the B.L.A.C.K. Student Success Program i
 nvite you to a compelling book discussion series featuring Black Birds in t
 he Sky: The Story and Legacy of the 1921 Tulsa Race Massacre by award-winni
 ng author Brandy Colbert. Together\, we’ll explore history\, memory\, and t
 he lasting impact of this pivotal moment in American history. The book disc
 ussion series takes place on Thursday\, January 29\, February 5\, 12\, and 
 19 at the DP Learning Commons\, Room 2425\, from 12 - 2:00 p.m. \n\n \n\nA 
 special author visit takes place on February 26 from 12:30 - 2:00 p.m. in t
 he Student Center\, Room 1530\, and via Zoom. Please register.\n\n \n\nBrin
 g your lunch\, your questions\, and join us for a meaningful conversation a
 nd learning. All are welcome!
DTEND:20260226T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T170247Z
DTSTART:20260226T183000Z
GEO:42.054993;-87.886683
LOCATION:Des Plaines Campus\, 2425
SEQUENCE:0
