BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Arts and Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:Jack H. Breslow (1927-2023)\, born in New York\, studied at the
  Académie Julian in Paris and the Art Students League in New York City. A p
 rolific studio artist\, Breslow gained recognition for his science fiction 
 book illustrations\, as well as his work on advertising campaigns\, movie p
 osters\, and magazine covers.\n\n \n\nThis exhibition marks the first publi
 c presentation of Breslow’s black-and-white works on paper\, unveiling a se
 ries of fantastical\, metaphysical imagery infused with botanical motifs an
 d expressive rock formations.\n\n \n\nThe Public Reception takes place on T
 hursday\, February 5\, 2026\, 5 - 8 p.m.\n\n \n\nViewings take place from F
 ebruary 5 to March 27\, 2026\, during regular museum hours.
DTSTAMP:20260311T170247Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260307
GEO:42.054993;-87.886683
LOCATION:Des Plaines Campus\, Koehnline Museum of Art
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Jack H. Breslow: Visual Metaphysics in Black and White
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50816144476600
URL:https://events.oakton.edu/event/jack-h-breslow-visual-metaphysics-in-bl
 ack-and-white
