BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Performing Arts Auditions,Performing Arts
DESCRIPTION:Killer Joe is an early play by award-winning playwright Tracy L
 etts. It tells the story of a young drug dealer named Chris who finds himse
 lf in desperate need of some cash. He and his father Ansel come up with the
  idea to murder Chris’ mother for her life insurance policy. They hire part
 -time hitman Joe Cooper to do the job\, but complications arise when Joe in
 sists on being paid in advance. Because the two men obviously can’t pay him
  before they receive their own dividends\, Chris draws up a plan that snare
 s his innocent sister\, Dottie\, into this wild scheme.\n\n\nCasting:  \nLo
 oking for a diverse cast to play 6 roles.  2-3 women ages 18-50\, and 3-4 m
 en\, ages 20-60.\nMonologues and script readings will be provided at the au
 dition.\n\n \n\nPerformance Dates and Times:   \nApril 18 at 7:30 p.m. \nAp
 ril 19 at 2:00 p.m.\n\n\nFor more information\, contact Daniel Cunningham a
 t dcunning@oakton.edu.
DTEND:20260307T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T170247Z
DTSTART:20260307T190000Z
GEO:42.054993;-87.886683
LOCATION:Des Plaines Campus\, TV Studio\, Room 1829
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Killer Joe\; A Staged Reading Auditions
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52127424811798
URL:https://events.oakton.edu/event/killer-joe-a-staged-reading-auditions
END:VEVENT
