BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Performing Arts
DESCRIPTION:By LaDarrion Williams    \nDirected by Veronda Carey\n\n \n\nOn
  February 29\, 1940\, the Oscars are set to make history in Hollywood\, but
  the night takes an unexpected turn when Bartender Arthur Brooks\, and his 
 best friend Dottie Hudson\, find themselves at a crossroads. As Academy Awa
 rd Nominee Hattie McDaniel unexpectedly opts out of the night’s grand event
 \, Arthur and Dottie are thrust into a frantic mission to convince her to a
 ttend and seize her historic victory. This gripping play delves into themes
  of race\, class\, gender\, and the shifting dynamics of Hollywood's golden
  age.\n\n \n\nPerformances:   \nMarch 12 at 12:30 p.m. and 7:30 p.m.  \n\n 
 \n\nTicket prices and purchasing options:\n\n$8 general admission\; $6 stud
 ents and seniors.\n\nTickets are available for purchase at the Box Office\,
  or by calling (847.635.1900).
DTEND:20260312T183000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T170247Z
DTSTART:20260312T173000Z
GEO:42.054993;-87.886683
LOCATION:Des Plaines Campus\, Studio Theater\, Room 1366
SEQUENCE:0
