BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:LGBTQIA+
DESCRIPTION:Join the LGBTQIA2+ Advisory Council for our Night of Noise Drag
  Show on Thursday\, April 9. Night of Noise is an annual campus celebration
  where students\, staff\, faculty\, and community members come together to 
 break the silence and uplift the diverse\, intersectional identities that e
 nrich our college. This event is in conjunction with the Day of (No) Silenc
 e on April 10\, in response to the increased attempts to erase LGBTQIA2+ in
 dividuals and voices from public life.\n\n \n\nAdmission is free. Cash tips
  for performers are welcome and encouraged.\n\n \n\nThe show features famil
 y-friendly performances from Chicago drag artists who always bring an unfor
 gettable experience. We hope to see you there!
DTEND:20260410T020000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T170248Z
DTSTART:20260410T000000Z
GEO:42.054993;-87.886683
LOCATION:Des Plaines Campus\, Studio One Theater
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Night of Noise Drag Show
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52055949630438
URL:https://events.oakton.edu/event/night-of-noise-drag-show
END:VEVENT
