BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Performing Arts
DESCRIPTION:By Tracy Letts\nDirected by Michael Berkson and John Frisco\n\n
  \n\nKiller Joe tells the story of a young drug dealer named Chris who find
 s himself in desperate need of some cash. He and his father come up with th
 e idea to murder Chris’ mother for her life insurance policy. They hire par
 t-time hit-man to do the job\, but complications arise when he insists on b
 eing paid in advance. Because the two men obviously can’t pay him before th
 ey receive their own dividends\, Chris draws up a plan that snares his inno
 cent sister\, Dottie\, into this wild scheme. \n\n \n\nTicket prices and pu
 rchasing options:\n\n$8 general admission\; $6 students and seniors.\n\nTic
 kets are available for purchase at the Box Office\, or by calling 847.635.1
 900.
DTEND:20260419T013000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T170248Z
DTSTART:20260419T003000Z
GEO:42.054993;-87.886683
LOCATION:Des Plaines Campus\, 1366\, Studio Theater
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Killer Joe: A Staged Reading
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51878993260264
URL:https://events.oakton.edu/event/killer-joe-a-staged-reading
END:VEVENT
