BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Performing Arts,Six Piano Ensemble
DESCRIPTION:Founded and conducted by Glenna Sprague\, Oakton professor and 
 coordinator of music\, the Six Piano Ensemble has amazed and delighted sold
 -out audiences throughout the country. The group performs classical\, ragti
 me\, jazz and popular music as well as symphonic repertoire transcribed for
  the six pianos. The rich\, layered sound of the Ensemble is comparable to 
 that of an orchestra as the melody transfers from pianist to pianist. Widel
 y acknowledged as one of the most unique musical groups in the world\, crit
 ics from Vienna to Glasgow hail the Six Piano Ensemble as "innovative\," te
 chnically superb\," and" musical." Enjoy an extraordinary concert experienc
 e and get your tickets early for this annual event!  A reception will follo
 w the concert.\n\n \n\nTicket prices and purchasing options:\n\n$15 general
  admission\; $10 students and seniors\; $8 groups\n\nTickets are available 
 for purchase at the Box Office\, or by calling (847.635.1900).
DTEND:20260426T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T170248Z
DTSTART:20260426T200000Z
GEO:42.054993;-87.886683
LOCATION:Des Plaines Campus\, Footlik Theater\, Room 1344
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Oakton Six Piano Ensemble
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51809324323088
URL:https://events.oakton.edu/event/copy-of-oakton-six-piano-ensemble
END:VEVENT
