BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Arts and Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:This exhibition presents approximately seventy paintings create
 d in Northern Europe during the sixteenth and seventeenth centuries\, with 
 a particular emphasis on Dutch masters of the Golden Age. Among the many hi
 ghlights are works associated with Rembrandt’s circle\, including a piece b
 y his teacher Pieter Lastman and notable examples by his pupils Gerard Dou\
 , Ferdinand Bol\, and Govert Flinck. Also on view are three paintings by Ja
 n Steen\, the quintessential Dutch genre painter known for his vivid depict
 ions of everyday life. The entire collection was assembled over four decade
 s by Harlan J. Berk\, a Chicago-based coin dealer specializing in ancient n
 umismatics. Berk is the author of six books and numerous articles on the su
 bject\, and his discerning eye has brought together a remarkable array of N
 orthern European paintings that reflect both scholarly depth and personal p
 assion.\n\n \n\nThe Public Reception takes place on Thursday\, May 7\, 5 - 
 8 p.m.\n\n \n\nViewings take place from May 7 to June 26\, 2026\, during re
 gular museum hours.
DTEND:20260508T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T170248Z
DTSTART:20260507T220000Z
GEO:42.054993;-87.886683
LOCATION:Des Plaines Campus\, Koehnline Museum of Art
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Master Paintings from the Harlan J. Berk Collection
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50816265722187
URL:https://events.oakton.edu/event/master-paintings-from-the-harlan-j-berk
 -collection
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Ceremonies
DESCRIPTION:Please join Oakton College's Honors Program\, Women\, Gender\, 
 and Sexuality Studies\, Environmental Studies\, Great Books\, Jewish Studie
 s\, Global Studies and Peace and Social Justice Studies concentrations and 
 the Library as we hold our fourth annual Student Scholar Showcase and Acade
 mic Concentration Award Ceremony.    \n\n \n\nCome join us (in-person or vi
 rtually) as we recognize students who have completed the Honors Scholar des
 ignation and the above concentrations\, as well as honor the awardees from 
 each concentration. Come to congratulate your peers\, learn more about thei
 r scholarly and creative projects and enjoy light refreshments.\n\n \n\nPle
 ase RSVP by April 30. After registering\, you will receive an email confirm
 ation with the Zoom link to attend the event virtually.\n\n \n\nDid you com
 plete work in the Honors Program or any of the concentrations that you woul
 d like to share? Please use this form to submit it (please express interest
  by 4/15\, and submit all materials by 4/30).\n\n \n\nFor questions\, conta
 ct professors Charles Townsend (townsend@oakton.edu) or Lindsey Hewitt (lhe
 witt@oakton.edu).
DTEND:20260508T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T170248Z
DTSTART:20260507T230000Z
GEO:42.054993;-87.886683
LOCATION:Des Plaines Campus\, Student Center\, Room 1530
SEQUENCE:0
