BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Arts and Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:Veteran Illinois artist Mike Baur has been creating sculptural 
 works in the Chicago area since 1976. His pieces are featured in numerous p
 ublic spaces and museum collections\, including two works held by the Koehn
 line Museum of Art. This exhibition showcases sculptures inspired by the te
 xtures and forms of natural landscapes—often vast expanses interrupted by b
 oth organic and industrial elements. Baur’s work offers abstract interpreta
 tions of these environments\, frequently suggesting a horizontal orientatio
 n that reflects how natural forces can subdue vertical structures.\n\n \n\n
 The Public Reception takes place on Thursday\, July 2\, 5 - 8 p.m.\n\n \n\n
 Viewings take place from July 2 to September 25\, 2026\, during regular mus
 eum hours.
